# Conventions

## Before starting work

1. Check `SPRINT.md` for current scope — only work on in-scope or in-progress stories. **Keep it updated** (see `sprint.mdc`).
2. Check `CHANGELOG.md` **Unreleased** — do not re-implement shipped capabilities.
3. Check `BACKLOG.md` for story ID and acceptance criteria.
4. Cross-repo contracts: read `INTEGRATION.md` and pinned `schemas/` — do not change response shapes without parent PRD §26 approval.
5. Implementation rationale: read `DECISIONS.md`; **log new decisions automatically** (see `decisions.mdc`).
6. When a story ships: update `SPRINT.md` and `CHANGELOG.md` same session.
7. **Mac ↔ Windows handoff:** after App/Spike changes the user will test on Windows, **commit and push** in the same session per `git-sync.mdc`. Report branch + commit SHA in the reply.

## C#

- Nullable reference types enabled. Avoid `null!` without justification.
- Business logic in `EventPlatform.PrintRelay.Core` — UI projects orchestrate only.
- `RelayConstants` for magic numbers (poll interval, message max length, page dimensions).
- Async all the way for HTTP and WebView2; use `ConfigureAwait` appropriately in library code.

## API integration

- Auth: `Authorization: Bearer {relay_secret}` on poll/complete/fail.
- Fail body: `{ "message": "plain English" }` only; max 500 chars.
- Map HTTP errors to operator-safe messages in UI layer — no status codes in toasts.

## Secrets

- Relay secret stored locally after setup wizard — never in diagnostics export or logs.
- Setup code shown once in platform admin — Windows app decodes and persists secret only.

## Testing (definition of done)

- New Core logic → xUnit unit tests (must pass on macOS/Linux CI)
- Schema contract changes → update fixtures + `schemas/platform-pin.json`
- WebView2 / tray / MSI → manual verification checklist in story acceptance

## Scope discipline

Implement the story only. No MSI, telemetry, or post-MVP features without explicit request.
